	<title>LIBER DECIMUS</title>
	</head>
		<div type="textpart" subtype="section">
		<head>
		<title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.gorgon.gorgonis_fragmenta">
		GORGONIS FRAGMENTA
		</ref></title>
		</head>
			<div type="textpart" subtype="work">
			<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.gorgon.gorgonis_fragmenta.de_sacris_rhodiorum">
			ΠΕΡΙ ΤΩΝ ΕΝ ΡΟΔῼ ΘΥΣΙΩΝ
			</ref></title></ab>
			<div type="textpart" >
			<cit n="1">
				<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.gorgon.gorgonis_fragmenta.de_sacris_rhodiorum:1">
					<bibl> Athenaeus XV, p. 696, F:</bibl>
					<quote>
					Καὶ ὁ εἰς Πτολεμαῖον δὲ, τὸν πρῶτον Αἰγύπτου βασιλεύσαντα, παιάν ἐστιν, ὃν ᾄδουσι Ῥόδιοι· ἔχει γὰρ τὸ Ἰὴ παιὰν ἐπίφθεγμα, ὥς φησι Γόργων ἐν τῷ Περὶ τῶν ἐν Ῥόδῳ θυσιῶν.
					</quote>
					<note type="translation"> Illud item, quod in Ptolemaeum primum Aegypti regem canunt Rhodii, vere paean est: habet enim acclamationem, Ie Paean; ut ait Gorgon in libro De Rhodiorum sacris. </note>
					<note type="commentary">Libri Γεωργὸς, quod correxit Casaubonus. Γόργων nomen occurrit etiam in inscript. Attica ap. Boeckh. C. I I, p. 292, 32.</note>
				</ref>
			</cit>
			</div>
			<div type="textpart" >
			<cit n="2">
				<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.gorgon.gorgonis_fragmenta.de_sacris_rhodiorum:2">
					<bibl> Hesych.:</bibl>
					<quote>
					Καταρραπτίτης (codex Καταραπτίτης). Γόργων ἐν τῷ Περὶ θυσιῶν.
					</quote>
					<note type="translation"> Καταρραπτίτης. Gorgon in libro De sacris. </note>
					<note type="commentary"></note>
				</ref>
			</cit>
			</div>
			<div type="textpart" >
			<cit n="2">
				<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.gorgon.gorgonis_fragmenta.de_sacris_rhodiorum:2">
					<bibl> Hesych.:</bibl>
					<quote>
					Ἐπιπολιαῖος, Ἑρμῆς ἐν Ῥόδῳ, ὡς Γόργων ἱστορεῖ.
					</quote>
					<note type="translation"> Ἐπιπολιαῖος, Mercurius in Rhodo, ut Gorgon scribit. </note>
					<note type="commentary">Ceterum non de sacrificiis tantum, sed de aliis quoque rebus quae ad Rhodios pertinent, Gorgonem scripsisse colligas e schol. Pindari.</note>
				</ref>
			</cit>
			</div>
			<div type="textpart" >
			<cit n="3">
				<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.gorgon.gorgonis_fragmenta.de_sacris_rhodiorum:3">
					<bibl> Schol. Pindar. Ad Olymp. VII, 1 (quod carmen Diagorae Rhodio scriptum):</bibl>
					<quote>
					Ταύτην τὴν ᾠδὴν ἀνακεῖσθαί φησι Γόργων ἐν τῷ τῆς Λινδίας Ἀθηνᾶς ἱερῷ χρυσοῖς γράμμασιν.
					</quote>
					<note type="translation"> Hoc Pindari carmen aureis literis exaratum positum esse in fano Minervae Lindiae. </note>
					<note type="commentary">V. Boeckh. ad h. carmen. De Diagora cf. supra frgm. Apollae.</note>
				</ref>
			</cit>
			</div>
			</div>
